The paper discusses the need for an architectural solution to support the long-term evolution and maintenance of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also focuses on the use of Continuous Experimentation (CE) in cyber-physical systems, specifically in the automotive domain, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and embedded systems (cs.EM) categories. Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of adopting CE in self-driving vehicles, which may require human-computer interaction (cs.HC) considerations.
